               Welcome to our openSUSE Weekly News Repository

First of all we would like to introduce you to our SVN repository. The structure
looks like this:

* branches/
* tags/        Contain snapshots for each edition
* trunk/       Everything about OWN
    docs/      All Documentation about OWN @ DocBook
    en/        The English newsletter.
     .         README, Makefiles, chooser.py
     logos/    Contain pictures
     xml/      Contain the XML sources
     xslt/     Contain no editable content, only stylesheets
        fo/    Stylesheets for the FO output
        html/  Stylesheets for the HTML output
    
    de/        The German newsletter, same content as en/
    ja/        The Japanese newsletter, same content like en/


The "docs" directory contain different documents for the several target groups:

TUTORIAL     - Is a step-by-step explanation. It explains how you create the 
               wanted output
DEVEL        - Contains information about the process
BUILD        - Explains how you can compile our XML files with the help of XSLT
               stylesheet to get your output
TODO         - Place for plans, enhencements, errors in a stylesheet or 
               a layout problem


If you want to add your language, proceed as follows:

1. Register yourself at <http://developer.berlios.de/account/register.php>.
2. Write an e-mail to <saigkill@opensuse.org> and insert your account details.
3. Check out our repository and have fun! :-)


